HEADWORD: Hayward
<hw>Hay"ward</hw> <pr>(h⟦amac⟧"w⟦etil⟧rd)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[<ets>Hay</ets> a hedge + <ets>ward</ets>.]</ety> <def>An officer
who is appointed to guard hedges, and to keep cattle from breaking or
cropping them, and whose further duty it is to impound animals found
running at large.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Hazard</ent>⟦br⟧
